function checkIfLastCharIsALetter($txt) {
    $words = explode(" ", $txt);
    if (count($words) == 1) {
        return false;
    }
    $lastWord = end($words);
    return ctype_alpha(substr($lastWord, -1));
}
```

This function first splits the input string into an array of words using `explode()`. If there is only one word in the input string (i.e., no spaces), it returns false because there are no non-alphabetic characters at the end of a single word.

If there are multiple words, it uses `end()` to get the last word and checks if its last character is alphabetic using `ctype_alpha()`. If it is, it returns true; otherwise, it returns false.

