```php
function checkIfLastCharIsALetter($txt) {
  // Remove all whitespace from the beginning and end of the string
  $str = trim($txt);

  // Check if there are any non-alphabetical characters at the end of the string
  if (preg_match('/[^a-zA-Z]$/', $str)) {
    return false;
  } else {
    return true;
  }
}
```

This function uses regular expressions to check for non-alphabetical characters at the end of the string. If there are no matches, it means that the last character is an alphabetical character and not part of a word.
